Sounds like the core element of the game is the shooting, so id say focus on that primarily, depending how engaging, and complex you want it to be - more complex systems means more requirement on teamwork of the other players, less complex means that players can make solo plays and "carry" a lot easier (this is where Overwatch's philosophy of everyone will just be nice to eachother and work as a team well for a common victory falls apart, partly)

So with that said, if your going FPS perspective, you can do more engaing reload systems, or even shooting systems, like the ones where you have to time it just right with the circle popup for fast reload, or holding down left click will eventually "overheat" your gun, or racking up a combo of lets say 30 kills in a row will "overcharge" your gun, requireing no ammo for a few seconds, or even the more combos you get the more stacked damage you do up to a certain amount, the next shot is double the damage if you land a killing blow headshot, etc - these are much more complex mechanics that require the player to deeply understand the shooting system of the game, and how every gun works, but it depends how complex you wanna go

I think then that should be the main focal point to design, perfect and really make fun first, above everything else - I donno how far along the actual project is, but if it's not started yet, I'd say do this feature in isolation (maybe with the character controller and mouse look if that's already implemented), figure out all the different (for lack of better term) effects combat can have - and when I say effects, in this case I mean the active reload, the cooldown/overheat, the blunt melee converting the gun and shoot mechanic into a stock and swing mechanic, the bonus damage or whatever, etc, all of those, I'm gonna call "effects" in this case, cause I donno a better descriptive word atm o.o
Once you have that basically perfected, exactly how you want it, you'll already have the "unique" element of the game, which is in the fun of the system(s), or in the complexity of them, if your going for high risk high reward style combat, where NOT playing safe, and maximizing your weapons to point of almost jamming, almost overheating, etc, is optimal, very rewarding if pulled off right, but very detrimental if you fuck it up - I don't remember the game, I think it's Doom? You get a small percentage of your health back if you do a melee killing blow on a enemy, but it plays this kinda "finisher" animation, where you cant move during it, and are still 100% vulnerable to being hit by enemies while it's active
You could do something similar to that for example, for maybe health regen, maybe it's a "pick pocket" for a small reserve of ammo, maybe it just guarantees a insta kill on mobs less than 30% health, or something else, that adds a reason to not play the "easy" way, if that's the style of play you want o.o (sorry, very lengthy)

